
muhhwm
======
A tiling window manager for X11.

muhhwm organises windows into tags and namespaces. Each namespace (study,
code, free) has its own independent set of six tags, letting you keep
separate contexts without interference. Three layouts are available:
tiled, monocle, and floating.

The status bar is handled by muhhbar, a separate process found under
tools/muhhbar/.


Requirements
------------
- Xlib header files
- Xft
- fontconfig


Installation
------------
Edit config.mk if needed, then:

    make clean install

This installs muhhwm to /usr/local/bin by default. Run as root if
necessary.

Copy config.def.h to config.h and edit it before building:

    cp config.def.h config.h


Running
-------
Add this to your .xinitrc:

    exec muhhwm

To start on a specific display:

    DISPLAY=:1 exec muhhwm


Configuration
-------------
All configuration is done in config.h before compilation. Keybindings
are in binds.h. There is no runtime config file.

See muhhwm(1) for keybinding reference.


